[normal]Parties shall assure to the child who is capable of forming his or her own views the right to 
[normal]express those views freely in all matters affectin
[normal]g the child, the views of the child being 
[normal]given due weight in accordance with the age and maturity of the child.
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]For this purpose the child shall in particular be provided the opportunity to be heard in any judicial and administrative proceedings 
[normal]affecting the child, either directly, or through a representative or appropriate body, in a manner consistent with the procedural rules of national law.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We also refer the Committee to 
[normal]Baroness Hale at paragraph 23 of 
[normal]ZH (Tanzania) (FC) (Apellant) V[bold]Secretary of State for the Home Department [2011] UKSC 4[bold] which 
[normal]states,  'This is a binding obligation 
[normal]in international law, and the spirit, if not the precise language, has also been translated into our 
[normal]national law.
